headline: Goldman Sachs downgrades Phillips 66 to ‘neutral’ as it sees limited upside
summary: Investing.com -- Goldman Sachs downgraded Phillips 66 (NYSE:PSX) to Neutral from Buy as it sees limited upside after the stock’s 14% year-to-date outperformance relative to refining peers. The firm maintained its price target of $132, implying an 8% total return from current levels.
